##Zhang Boli: new cases in Wuhan are expected to be "cleared" by the end of March

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

People's Daily client

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
All pictures in this article are People's Daily Pictures

On March 3, Zhang Boli, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and President of the Tianjin University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, gave an exclusive interview to the People's Daily New Media in Wuhan.

What will happen next in the epidemic control situation? When will everyone be able to "take off their masks" ? Will the new coronavirus become normal and become chronic? Look at this has been fighting the "epidemic" Front for more than a month of veterans say.

When will new cases be "zeroed out" ?

Zhang Boli: we have analyzed the evolution of the epidemic data, at present, the country except Hubei other regions, the end of February new cases basically "clear zero" ;

The province, with the exception of Wuhan, is expected to close to zero by mid-march;

Wuhan is on track to achieve a basic "clean slate" by the end of March.

From the overall development trend of the epidemic, yes. However, "zero out" is not absolute, occasionally there will be a few new cases.

When can I "take off my mask" ?

Zhang Boli: It is estimated that at the end of April, except Hubei, other provinces and cities in China can basically take off masks to resume normal life and production order. Hubei Province, especially Wuhan, may be about a month later than the rest of the country. However, I do not advocate so anxious to take off the mask, even if the resumption of work to resume production, restore normal order, the mask or slowly pick better. Even if the whole country "zero" , less gathering, frequent hand-washing, wearing masks good habits, but also to maintain a period of time. After all, the second half of the epidemic situation abroad is still very serious, to prevent imported cases.

I hope that we do not focus too much on when to take off the mask on this issue, to develop good living habits is the most important.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In Wuhan more than a month, what did you do?

Zhang Boli: When I first arrived in Wuhan on January 27, the situation was very serious and complicated: Patients and non-patients mixed together, feverish, observant, close-knit, suspicious, many of these "four groups of people" were not isolated and very confused. Large hospitals are crowded, waiting in line for hours to see the sick, confirmed cases can not be admitted to hospital, a bed hard to get..

At that time, we proposed to the Central Guidance Group, hierarchical classification management, centralized isolation, separate processing. At the same time, the diagnosis of patients should also be classified management, mild, severe treatment separately, can occupy schools, hotels, so that can effectively use limited health resources. However, at that time, many patients because there is no diagnosis, there is no effective treatment, but was simply isolated, emotional panic, treatment helpless. At that time, we suggested, based on past experience, that all of the "four categories of people" should be given Chinese medicine, because Chinese medicine is effective in treating both the common cold, influenza and new coronary pneumonia. First take medicine to stabilize the mood, a day or two fever, there is confidence.

Later, as more and more patients were diagnosed, one bed was hard to find and could not be collected, experts suggested setting up a shelter hospital to treat patients with mild illness. Professor Liu Qingquan and I wrote a letter of request, put forward the Chinese medicine into the shelter, the Chinese medicine undertakes the shelter hospital. With the approval of the Central Guidance Group, we formed the first TCM medical team, with 209 TCM experts from Tianjin, Jiangsu, Henan, Hunan and Shaanxi, to set up Jiangxia District's shelter hospital, which mainly used TCM comprehensive treatment. After gaining experience, almost all the shelter hospitals now use traditional Chinese medicine.

At present, the focus of the work is on the treatment of seriously ill patients. The Central Guidance Team has issued instructions to set up a joint Chinese and Western Medicine Consultation Group to conduct one-on-one consultation for seriously ill patients in Wuhan and to establish a one-on-one consultation plan that includes Chinese medicine. After several rounds of consultation, it still seems to be effective, the death toll in Wuhan has gradually dropped from 100 to dozens.

Now, we're looking at convalescent patients. Some discharged patients, especially the critically ill, have rehabilitation problems. Some discharge, but there are symptoms, cough, shortness of breath, palpitations, fatigue, and so on; some pulmonary infection exudate absorption is not complete, some immune dysfunction. We have set up a new rehabilitation clinic in Hubei Integrated Hospital of Traditional Chinese and Western medicine and Wuhan Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine to manage and treat these patients. With the support of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and relevant units, we have also organized the Wuhan Union Hospital to jointly set up a rehabilitation management platform for medical personnel of the new infectious diseases crown in Hubei Province, which will be the task for the next year or two.

How to look at this epidemic, on the strong debate between Chinese and Western medicine?

Zhang Boli: In this war "epidemic" , Chinese medicine and Western medicine is very harmonious. Especially in the process of rescuing critically ill patients, the western medicine is the main, the Chinese medicine is the auxiliary, but sometimes the auxiliary also plays the key role, already had many examples. The medical team of Chinese medicine and Western medicine do not distinguish you and me, who has the means who is on, can save the patient's life, this is our common goal.

At a time when the epidemic is so severe, it is often outsiders who are still arguing about who is strong and who is weak, boring and pointless. Chinese medicine and Western medicine have their own advantages, complementary advantages, human life is greater than the day, can save life is the most important.

Jiangxia District, what's the status of the MED Bay?

Zhang Boli: So far, Jiangxia District's shelter hospital has treated more than 500 patients, mainly with mild illness, accounting for 70% to 80% . More than 200 of them have been discharged. More than 100 patients are due to be discharged soon.

The best part is that none of the patients currently admitted to Jiangxia District are in critical condition, and none of the staff are infected.

Now, what's the status of the infected paramedics?

Chamberlain: Health Care Workers were infected, mostly in January. At that time, the patients were highly concentrated, the order was disordered, the medical staff were working at full load and high intensity, and the protective materials were not enough.

Now the protective measures, supplies have followed, the first-line medical staff's workload has also lightened, has been infected the situation to be few.

At present, most of the infected medical staff has been discharged from the hospital, there are still a part of the treatment. We will also set up a health management platform for infected medical personnel, to track their health status in the next one to two years, with integrated Chinese and Western medicine intervention to help them recover better. We hope to be able to provide the necessary assistance to infected health care workers in return for their efforts and sacrifice.

Will the new coronavirus become normal and become chronic?

Zhang Boli: whether the new coronavirus will be normalized or not, it is difficult to say at present, we need to continue to strengthen the current and basic research, after all, we have a limited understanding of it.

However, the impact of the coronavirus on human society will never end. It has been relatively benign for most of its existence since its discovery in the 1960s, but several mutations in the past two decades have led to large-scale epidemics and heavy losses. Therefore, I advocate to continue to study the mechanism of coronavirus infection, research and development of broad-spectrum anti-coronavirus drugs, so as not to change. And we're working on that right now.

Compared with SARS, where is the difficulty in treating new-crown pneumonia?

Zhang Boli: compared with SARS, the new coronavirus is more "cunning" , more "changeable" , but also more "unpredictable.

At the beginning, it doesn't seem to be that serious, but at a certain stage, it goes downhill. The new coronavirus is more transmissible than SARS, and the number of cases and deaths are much more than SARS. And, the patient after cure can appear"repeatedly", have certain proportion of patient after discharge again"Fu Yang". Rehabilitation of critically ill patients is also more complicated than SARS.

But we still want to have confidence, after all, discharged from the hospital, "Fu Yang" is a minority of patients. Moreover, "Fu Yang" patients with treatment is also relatively easy, the basic treatment of a few days will be "turned negative. Rehabilitation will also be the focus of future research.

What lessons should we draw from this outbreak?

Zhang Boli: First of all, to strengthen the source of governance. To put an end to all wild animal market transactions, strictly prohibit the consumption of terrestrial wild animals. The lessons of this epidemic are so profound that we must learn them and not forget them as we did with SARS.

Secondly, the existing "law of the People's Republic of China on the Prevention and control of infectious diseases" also needs to be amended. This outbreak has exposed a big problem, the outbreak has emerged, who will report? To whom? Now the mechanism is not smooth, layer upon layer report, layer upon layer audit, layer upon layer desalination, to the central decay flavor, affect the central decision-making. In retrospect, the spread of the disease from person to person became apparent in late December and early January of last year. At that time also said that is "limited human transmission" , "situation under control" , there is a problem, lost the best time for prevention and control.

Moreover, the health capacity of grass-roots communities is obviously inadequate. So many people, a fever on the big hospital run, if the community health care facilities are strong enough to play a "blocking intervention" role, the epidemic may be effectively controlled in the early, strong grass-roots to really landed.

In addition, the concentration of detection authority and the shortage of reagent boxes seriously affect the diagnosis and treatment, and the obvious shortage of prevention and control materials, deployment mechanism lag, emergency system response and operation need to be greatly improved.

Finally, I would like to remind that after the epidemic, do not forget Chinese medicine, or to continue to promote the cause of Chinese medicine development. In the recent china-who Epidemic Situation Inspection Expert Group did not have the traditional Chinese medicine expert, in the epidemic report, the traditional Chinese medicine has not covered, this is very regrettable.
